<h2>General Google Reviews Statistics</h2>
<p>Google dominates the online review space. No other platform comes close in volume, reach, or influence on purchase decisions.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Google reviews platform market share showing Google at 73 percent" src="/images/blog/google-reviews-platform-market-share.webp" /></p>
<p><strong>1. Google hosts 73% of all online reviews.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/online-review-statistics/">DemandSage, 2026</a>
That makes Google the single largest review platform by a wide margin. Yelp holds 6%, TripAdvisor 3%, and Facebook 3%.</p>
<p><strong>2. 81% of consumers check Google reviews before visiting a business.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/online-review-statistics/">DemandSage, 2026</a>
Google is the first stop for most buyers. If your <a href="/blog/optimize-google-business-profile/">Google Business Profile</a> has no reviews, you lose 4 out of 5 potential customers before they even visit your website.</p>
<p><strong>3. 129,087 verified companies actively use Google Reviews as of 2026.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://data.landbase.com/technology/google-reviews/">Landbase, 2026</a>
That number keeps growing as businesses recognize the revenue impact.</p>
<p><strong>4. Consumers use an average of 6 different review platforms before making a decision.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.brightlocal.com/research/local-consumer-review-survey/">BrightLocal, 2026</a>
Google is the starting point. But buyers cross-reference on Facebook, Apple Maps, and industry-specific sites.</p>
<p><strong>5. Apple Maps review usage nearly doubled from 14% to 27% in one year.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.brightlocal.com/research/local-consumer-review-survey/">BrightLocal, 2026</a>
Apple Maps is growing fast as a review platform. Businesses that only focus on Google miss an expanding audience.</p>
