<h2>Consumer Trust and Review Reading Statistics</h2>
<p>Consumers read reviews more often and trust them more deeply than ever. The 2026 data shows a clear acceleration.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Google reviews consumer trust statistics showing 97 percent read reviews and 81 percent check Google" src="/images/blog/google-reviews-consumer-trust-stats.webp" /></p>
<p><strong>6. 97% of consumers read reviews for local businesses.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.brightlocal.com/research/local-consumer-review-survey/">BrightLocal, 2026</a>
This is near-universal behavior. Only 3% of buyers skip reviews entirely.</p>
<p><strong>7. 41% of consumers "always" read reviews when browsing for businesses.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.brightlocal.com/research/local-consumer-review-survey/">BrightLocal, 2026</a>
This jumped from 29% in 2025. The "always" cohort grew by 41% in a single year.</p>
<p><strong>8. 88% of customers trust Google reviews as much as personal recommendations.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://wiserreview.com/blog/google-review-statistics/">WiserReview, 2026</a>
A stranger on Google carries the same weight as a friend. That is a staggering level of trust.</p>
<p><strong>9. 93% of consumers say reviews influence their purchasing decisions.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/online-review-statistics/">DemandSage, 2026</a>
Reviews are not optional reading. They directly change buying behavior.</p>
<p><strong>10. Consumers read an average of 10 reviews before trusting a business.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/online-review-statistics/">DemandSage, 2026</a>
Businesses with fewer than 10 <a href="/blog/google-reviews-guide/">Google reviews</a> face a trust gap that costs them sales.</p>
<p><strong>11. 74% of consumers only pay attention to reviews from the last 3 months.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.brightlocal.com/research/local-consumer-review-survey/">BrightLocal, 2026</a>
Old reviews lose credibility fast. A steady stream of <a href="/blog/get-more-google-reviews-local-business/">new reviews</a> matters more than a large but stale count.</p>
<p><strong>12. 32% of consumers want reviews from the last 2 weeks.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.brightlocal.com/research/local-consumer-review-survey/">BrightLocal, 2026</a>
This is up from 20% in 2025. Recency expectations keep accelerating.</p>
<p><strong>13. Consumers spend an average of 13 minutes and 45 seconds reading reviews.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/online-review-statistics/">DemandSage, 2026</a>
Reviews are not a quick glance. Buyers invest real time evaluating businesses through review content.</p>
