<h2>Fake Review Statistics</h2>
<p>Fake reviews remain a growing concern. Consumers are getting better at spotting them, and they punish businesses caught using them.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Fake Google review statistics showing 10.7 percent of Google reviews are estimated fake" src="/images/blog/google-reviews-fake-reviews-stats.webp" /></p>
<p><strong>40. 10.7% of Google reviews are estimated to be fake.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/online-review-statistics/">DemandSage, 2026</a>
Roughly 1 in 10 Google reviews is fraudulent. Yelp sits at 7.1% and TripAdvisor at 5.2%.</p>
<p><strong>41. 82% of consumers have encountered a fake review in the past year.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/online-review-statistics/">DemandSage, 2026</a>
Fake reviews are widespread enough that most buyers have seen them. Learn how to <a href="/blog/handle-fake-google-reviews/">handle fake Google reviews</a> to protect your business.</p>
<p><strong>42. 67% of consumers consider fake reviews a major problem.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/online-review-statistics/">DemandSage, 2026</a>
Trust is fragile. Businesses caught with fake reviews face severe reputation damage.</p>
<p><strong>43. 97% of consumers want consequences for businesses that post fake reviews.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.brightlocal.com/research/local-consumer-review-survey/">BrightLocal, 2026</a>
Consumers demand accountability. Platform bans and penalties are expected.</p>
<p><strong>44. 62% of consumers avoid brands that practice review censorship.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/online-review-statistics/">DemandSage, 2026</a>
Deleting or hiding negative reviews backfires. Transparency wins trust.</p>
